oc:kn_5bc19c5e a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When creating OAuth2 credential files (Step 3)" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never add an `authenticate` block or `test` block to the OAuth2 credential file — the `oAuth2Api` base class handles Bearer token injection and the OAuth dance validates the credential automatically." ;
    oc:hasRationale "The oAuth2Api base machinery already provides these capabilities; duplicating them causes conflicts." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_9a105383 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:PreFlightCheck ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Before starting credential creation" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Before implementation, verify: node directory exists at `packages/nodes-base/nodes/{NODE_NAME}/`, existing credentials are identified, and package.json registration pattern is understood." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Missing any prerequisite leads to broken file paths or registration failures." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_a011ab17 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Standard ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When creating credential files with scope configuration" ;
    oc:directiveContent "`defaultScopes` at module level is the single source of truth — it must populate both the `enabledScopes` default and the `scope` expression fallback. Update it in one place only." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Duplicating scope values in multiple places leads to drift and broken authorization." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_b8be6c7e a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When updating GenericFunctions.ts (Step 6)" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Distinguish between standard services (token works directly against instance URL) and gateway services (token scoped for gateway URL, requires cloudId/workspace ID lookup after token exchange). Use the Atlassian pattern as reference for gateway services." ;
    oc:hasRationale "The routing logic differs fundamentally between these two patterns — choosing wrong breaks API calls." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_d81747a1 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:RequiresHumanClarification ;
    oc:appliesToContext "During argument parsing and endpoint research (Steps 0 and 2)" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Ask the user for clarification when: (1) NODE_NAME is ambiguous from the argument, (2) whether scopes should be customizable is unclear, (3) OAuth2 endpoints cannot be confidently determined from documentation." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Guessing wrong on these decisions leads to incorrect credential configurations that are hard to fix later." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_deb80d4f a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When updating node files (Step 7)" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never change the `default` value of the version/auth parameter — existing workflows must not be affected by the new OAuth2 option." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Changing defaults breaks backward compatibility for users with existing workflows." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_ef69ae2d a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When custom scopes are enabled (Step 5)" ;
    oc:directiveContent "When CUSTOM_SCOPES is enabled, the credential name MUST be added to `GENERIC_OAUTH2_CREDENTIALS_WITH_EDITABLE_SCOPE` in `packages/cli/src/constants.ts` or n8n will delete the user's custom scope on OAuth2 reconnect." ;
    oc:hasRationale "The CLI uses this allowlist to decide which credentials preserve user-modified scopes across reconnections." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

